Trade/Device Name(s): FORA G71a Blood Glucose Monitoring System
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for FORA G71a and TD-4274 blood glucose monitoring systems using electrochemical biosensor technology
Indications for Use Summary: Quantitative measurement of glucose in fresh capillary whole blood from finger and alternative sites (palm, forearm, upper arm, calf, thigh) for use at home or by healthcare professionals to aid in monitoring diabetes control; not for diagnosis or screening of diabetes, nor for neonates.
